                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.5151 Williams Mission/24: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-07-17T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 17, 1934—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>83. For Doctor Williams. Recent developments in the exchange situation in Uruguay
                    prejudicial to American interests make it seem highly important that you visit
                    Montevideo and study the problem there. I very much hope that you will find it
                    possible to do so, even though this may mean extending your trip 10 days or 2
                    weeks longer.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
